		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Out of such a limited data set, the odds running into a collision have got to be virtually zilch unless it was intentional. Considering that all the data comes straight from CopyNES, one would have to go thru some trouble in order to supply their own data. Either one would have to load their data onto a RAM cart and dump it, or hack the program while running. And why anyone would want to do this to begin with, is beyond me <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />
<br />
<br />Besides, I was under the impression that MD5 sums could be faked as well...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


