	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />CRC32 and MD5 are near useless for file identification nowadays; stick with SHA-1 for now. (SHA-1 is Nintendo approved, as it's used by the Nintendo DS firmware to verify digital signatures on DS Download Play binaries.)
<br />
<br />Yes, it would probably be best to go back to the original dumps and SHA-1 them. In fact, it might be better to SHA-1 each 16 KB PRG ROM segment and each 8 KB CHR ROM segment for easier early detection of hacked versions.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


